{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Enumeration","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"PIDFile","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"symbolKind":"enum","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PIDFile"}],"role":"symbol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"text":". The file contains the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"process ID of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"text":" process that owns the VM.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Other commands (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"text":") read the PID file to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","text":"PID File Lifecycle","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook stop","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)"},{"text":" detects stale PID files by checking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether the recorded process is still running.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"title":"Type Properties","generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/read(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/remove(from:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/terminate(bundleURL:gracePeriod:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/write(to